"5:41:41" : {s: 5, a: 41, w: 41, r: "", t: "وَمَن", l: "مَن", lc: 871, tl: "waman", lb: "যেই ব্যাক্তি",e: "And (for) whom", b: "এবং যে", i: "dan barangsiapa", f: 188, rm: ""},
"5:41:42" : {s: 5, a: 41, w: 42, r: "رود", t: "يُرِدِ", l: "أَرَادَ", lc: 139, tl: "yuridi", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "intends", b: "তিনি  চান", i: "menghendaki", f: 3, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.)."},
